 Topic 
 ===========================================================
 -> Topic is a bucket of message where services may place or read the messages.
 -> A topic is similar like a folder and the messages are similar like files in that folder.
 -> Topics are multiple producer and multiple subscriber.
 -> Message can be read many time as needed. because it store messages in a memory box.
 -> A topic can also have multiple partition. this allows multiple consumer read that message parallel.
 -> Topics are partitioned for scalability and replicated for fault tolerance.
 
 What is a Kafka Cluster?
 =====================================================
 -> A Kafka cluster is a group of Kafka brokers (servers) working together to store, manage, and distribute data (messages).
 
 Producer
 =======================================
 -> A producer send/write messages to the topic within the cluster.
 
 Consumer
 =======================================
 -> A consumer is read the messages from the Kafka cluster.
 -> A consumer can read the data in same time from multiple broker.
 
 Broker
 ====================================
 -> A kafka broker is a bridge between producer and consumer. if a producer produce one message to the cluster, it is sent to the 
    kafka server. A kafka broker allows consumer to fetch that message by topic.
 -> All broker are maintained inside Kafka cluster.
 -> To maintain the load balance of the kafka cluster it have multiple kafka broker.
 
 Partitions
 =====================================
 -> The messages is divided in to small subparts/ replicated known as partitions.
 -> Each partitions carries data.
 
 Zookeeper
 ====================================
 -> Kafka broker use Zookeepeer for managing and cordinating purpose.
 -> There are multiple Zookeepeer inside cluster.
 -> A user does not directly interact with zoopeeper, but via broker.
 -> No kafka serveris run without zookeeper server. It is mandatory to run the zookeeper server.
 
