 3. Explain Kafka Architecture.
 =====================================================================================
	Producer
	Publishes messages to Kafka topics.
	
	Consumer
	Reads messages from Kafka topics.
	
	Topic
	A category where messages are stored.
	
	Partition
	Topics are divided into partitions for parallel processing.
	
	Broker
	Kafka server responsible for storing data.
	
	Consumer Group
	Multiple consumers working together.
	
	ZooKeeper
	Used in older Kafka versions for cluster coordination.
	
	KRaft
	Newer Kafka versions use KRaft instead of ZooKeeper.
	
