 13. How does Kafka guarantee message delivery?
 ======================================================================================
	Three modes:
	
	At most once
	Message may be lost.
	
	At least once
	No loss but duplicates possible.
	
	Exactly once
	No loss and no duplicates.
	
 14. What is Exactly Once Semantics?
 ===============================================================================
	Kafka ensures messages are processed only once using:
	
	Idempotent Producer
	   Configuration :
	   enable.idempotence=true
	   
 15. What is Idempotent Producer?
 ===========================================================================
  -> Prevents duplicate messages caused by retries.
        enable.idempotence=true
        
 16. What is the acknowledgment (acks) setting?
 =============================================================================
	acks=0
		Producer doesn't wait.
		Fastest but risky.
	acks=1
		Leader acknowledges.
		Balanced approach.
	acks=all
		All ISR replicas acknowledge.
		Safest.
		
 17. What is Consumer Rebalancing?
 ===========================================================================
	Occurs when:
	
	New consumer joins.
	Consumer leaves.
	Partitions change.
	
	Kafka redistributes partitions among consumers.
	
 18. What causes duplicate messages?
 ==============================================================================
	Producer retries
	Consumer processing failure
	Offset commit issues
	
	Solutions:
	
	Idempotent producer
	Exactly-once semantics
	
 19. Auto Commit vs Manual Commit?
 =============================================================================
   Auto Commit
      enable.auto.commit=true
      
      Kafka commits offsets automatically.
      Risk: Message loss.
      
   Manual Commit
      consumer.commitSync();
      
      Commit after successful processing.
      Preferred in banking applications.
      
 20. commitSync() vs commitAsync()
 =========================================================================
	commitSync()
	   Blocks execution
	   Reliable
	commitAsync()
	   Non-blocking
	   Faster
	   
