 33. Why manual commit in banking systems?
 ============================================================================
 -> If we are using auto commit Kafka may commit the offset before processing completes. 
 
    With manual commit:
               consumer.commitSync();
               Offset is committed only after successful processing.
               
 34. Difference between RabbitMQ and Kafka.
 ==============================================================================
	| Feature           | Kafka               | RabbitMQ                     |
	| ----------------- | ------------------- | ---------------------------- |
	| Model             | Distributed log     | Traditional message queue    |
	| Throughput        | Very high           | Moderate                     |
	| Message Retention | Configurable        | Deleted after acknowledgment |
	| Ordering          | Per partition       | Queue based                  |
	| Replay Messages   | Yes                 | Limited                      |
	| Scalability       | Excellent           | Moderate                     |
	| Use Case          | Event streaming     | Task queues                  |
	| Storage           | Disk-based          | Memory + Disk                |
	| Consumer Offset   | Managed by consumer | Managed by broker            |
	
